VIRAL HEMORRHAGIC DISEASE, RABBITS - CUBA (03)
**********************************************
Date: Fri, 18 Jul 1997 13:57:09 -0400
From: ProMED-mail <promed@usa.healthnet.org>
Via: Dorothy Preslar <dpreslar@fas.org>
[see
Viral hemorrhagic disease, rabbits - Cuba 970627164509
Viral hemorrhagic disease, rabbits - Cuba (02) 970704155234]
Source: Translation of a fax received on 11 July 1997 from Dr E.F. Serrano
Ramirez, Director General, Institute of Veterinary Medicine, Ministry of
Agriculture, Havana
End of previous report period: 25 June 1997
End of this report period: 9 July 1997.
New outbreaks:
Location No. of outbreaks
Havana Province 1
Havana City Province 2

Total number of outbreaks identified since 1 January 1997: fifteen (15).
Total number of animals in the new outbreaks:
susceptible 14,801
cases 1,606
deaths 1,606
destroyed 7,321
slaughtered 5,874

Diagnosis:
A. Laboratory where diagnosis was made: National Centre for Epizootiology
and Diagnosis.
B. Diagnostic tests used: clinical and laboratory (anatomopathological,
haemagglutination with human type O erythrocytes).
C. Causal agent: viral haemorrhagic disease of rabbits virus.
Epidemiology:
A. Source of agent/origin of infection: investigations under way.
B. Mode of spread: certain protection measures not respected.
C. Other epidemiological details: the last outbreak was confirmed on 4 July
1997.
Control measures during reporting period: stamping out; control of
invertebrate vectors; diagnostic testing; quarantine and movement control
inside the country; vaccination prohibited.
